A 20-year-old man has cut his own throat while standing in the dock after being given a prison sentence.

The defendant, understood to be Gary Bell, was in court two of Kirklees Magistrates' Court in Huddersfield, West Yorkshire, this afternoon when he is said to have taken a  blade from his pocket and ran it across his neck.

The horrifying incident unfolded after Bell, from nearby Milnsbridge, was sentenced to a total of 16 weeks in jail for three charges of assault by beating and two of criminal damage.

