The court was then cleared and paramedics then took him to Leeds General Infirmary where he is currently being treated.

West Yorkshire Police confirmed that the man was alive but the extent of his injuries are currently unknown. 

A spokesman said: 'We can confirm that a 20 year old man from Milnsbridge has sustained self-inflicted neck injuries while attending Huddersfield Magistrates Court just before three o'clock this afternoon.

